#  Task 1: Install and Authenticate GitHub CLI (gh)

### 1. Install GitHub CLI

Verify if it's already installed
```bash 
gh --version 
```
If installed, you'll see something like:
```bash 
anujrai@anujrai-mn4561 90DaysOfDevOps % gh --version 
gh version 2.93.0 (2026-05-27)
https://github.com/cli/cli/releases/tag/v2.93.0
anujrai@anujrai-mn4561 90DaysOfDevOps % 
```

If not installed

Using Homebrew:
```bash 
brew install gh
```
verify: 
```bash 
gh --version
```

### 2. Authenticate with GitHub

Run:
```bash 
gh auth login 
```
you'll be asked: 

GitHub.com or Enterprise?

```bash 
GitHub.com
```

Preferred Protocol?
```bash 
HTTPS
```
Authenticate Git?

Choose:
```
YES 
```
Login Method?

Choose:
```
Login with a web browser
```

You'll see:

```
First copy your one-time code: XXXX-XXXX
Press Enter to open https://github.com/login/device
```
- Open the browser and authorize.

